rt of"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recwcML6FMulTblKH","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"rec3CJaR6qJKZgcUA","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recUt3VRWj3MN5Pg0","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recVrmSzvxPuuzQ3v","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recNzNKGhPz5qS3Kc","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recJSfVnIcPibY6aX","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recIe4ffJFDzJDWBR","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recdiq65RtvGagXOn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"recTzP6VykOhwetgm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"reccUeZb53JJ02Lv9","label":"event"},{"source":"recXrEbk8Tb5ahtRa","target":"rec24EmrBZzGvOD2U","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recgwmiBEpyP7CfM8","ref":"Judg.16.1","text":"Then went Samson to Gaza, and saw there an harlot, and went in unto her.","year":-1120},{"id":"recf5SDm1LLvJdx83","ref":"Judg.16.2","text":"And it was told the Gazites, saying, Samson is come hither. And they compassed him in, and laid wait for him all night in the gate of the city, and were quiet all the night, saying, In the morning, when it is day, we shall kill him.","year":-1120},{"id":"rec6sEbEGNcdGRts8","ref":"Judg.16.3","text":"And Samson lay till midnight, and arose at midnight, and took the doors of the gate of the city, and the two posts, and went away with them, bar and all, and put them upon his shoulders, and carried them up to the top of an hill that is before Hebron.","year":-1120},{"id":"recPQVlmzGdLtdLQ4","ref":"Judg.16.4","text":"And it came to pass afterward, that he loved a woman in the valley of Sorek, whose name was Delilah.","year":-1120},{"id":"rec9TaeZqsTowMTUo","ref":"Judg.16.5","text":"And the lords of the Philistines came up unto her, and said unto her, Entice him, and see wherein his great strength lieth, and by what means we may prevail against him, that we may bind him to afflict him: and we will give thee every one of us eleven hundred pieces of silver.","year":-1120},{"id":"rec8FfJiIMs99ORY9","ref":"Judg.16.6","text":"And Delilah said to Samson, Tell me, I pray thee, wherein thy great strength lieth, and wherewith thou mightest be bound to afflict thee.","year":-1120},{"id":"rec8ziBLluX8WQCm0","ref":"Judg.16.7","text":"And Samson said unto her, If they bind me with seven green withs that were never dried, then shall I be weak, and be as another man.","year":-1120},{"id":"recfZbQtguKLBUfIj","ref":"Judg.16.8","text":"Then the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven green withs which had not been dried, and she bound him with them.","year":-1120}]}
